{"id":"numeric-submitted-at","severity":"HIGH","rule_id":"spec.invalid-input-accepted","file":"bin/cli.js","line":58,"message":"`if (typeof value === 'number') {` and `if (Number.isFinite(value) && !Number.isNaN(timestamp)) return timestamp;` accept numeric epoch values even though `submitted_at` must be an ISO date or timestamp. Probe `node bin/cli.js fulfill-wave --input /dev/stdin` with `submitted_at: 0` expected exit 2, empty stdout, and a JSON object on stderr; actual result was exit 0, empty stderr, and `{\"accepted\":[{\"id\":\"O-numeric-time\",\"allocations\":[]}],\"rejected\":[],\"remaining\":[]}` on stdout.","confidence":"high","criterion_ref":"Requirements: validate the entire input before allocating; order `submitted_at` parseable as an ISO date or timestamp; any violation is invalid input"}
# SUMMARY {"verdict":"NEEDS_WORK"}
